<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-05-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-05-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="497" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d497">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Russell</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-05-22"><hi rend="italic">May 22,
                                1901.</hi></date></dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 415.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 605, of the 3d instant, inclosing a copy of the note addressed by
                            the president of the State of Barcelona to the United States consular
                            agent at Barcelona apologizing for the latter’s arrest, also a copy of
                            Mr. Balz’s reply.</p>
                        <p>The Department awaits your reply to its No. 414, of the 4th instant,
                            which crossed your dispatch, relative to an expected explanation of the
                            failure to deliver the legation’s telegram to the consular agent.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">David J. Hill</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>